    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <h2 class="page-title">Transportation</h2>
        <h2>Venue</h2>
        <p>
            The main competition room is the Plenary at the Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre. There are also rooms for side events and relaxing within the venue.
	    <br>
            The Plenary is located within the Convention Centre.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        <img style="margin-bottom:10px;" src="https://mcec.com.au/-/media/mcec/images/visit/key-info/getting-there/mcec_tram.ashx" width="100%;" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-8">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0">
            <strong>Address</strong>: 1 Convention Centre Place, South Wharf.<br>
            <strong>Public Transportation</strong>: The Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre is located in the heart of Melbourne's South Wharf.
            <br><br>
            <span class="label metro-stop" style="margin-right:10px;">Train</span>   The closest train stations are Southern Cross station (9 minute walk), and Flinders Street station (12 minute walk).
			<br>
			<br>
			<span class="label metro-stop" style="margin-right:10px;">Tram on Clarendon</span>   Tram routes 96, 109 and 12 (Stop 124A Casino/MCEC) will all take you to the Clarendon Street entrance of the centre.
			<br>
			<br>
			<span class="label metro-stop" style="margin-right:10px;">Tram on Flinders</span>Tram routes 48 and 70 (Stop D5) take you to Flinders Street, a short walk away from the venue.
			<br>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <h2>Airport Connection</h2>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
        <iframe width="100%" height="250" id="gmap_canvas" src="https://maps.google.com/maps?q=melbourne%20airport&t=&z=9&ie=UTF8&iwloc=&output=embed" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" marginheight="10px" marginwidth="0"></iframe>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
        <p>
            <a href="https://www.melbourneairport.com.au/" target="_blank">Melbourne Airport</a>
            is located approximately 25 kilometres North-West of the city. The cheapest way to travel to the city is via the <a href="https://www.skybus.com.au/" target="_blank">SkyBus</a>, which departs frequently all 24 hours of the day. A one-way ticket costs 19.50 AUD.
			The SkyBus runs from the airport to Southern Cross railway station, which is only a 10 minute walk from the competition venue and surrounding areas.
		<br>
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0">
			<span class="label metro-stop" style="margin-right:10px;">Taxi and Uber</span><br><br>           
			If youâ€™re arriving with a group of three or more people, it may be more cost-effective to take a taxi or Uber. A ride from the airport to the city normally costs between 50 AUD and 65 AUD depending on the time of day.
        </p>

    </div>
</div>
<br>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <h2>General Travel Information</h2>
        <ul class="ul">
            <li>
               Public transport within Melbourne is run by <a href="https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/getting-around/visiting-melbourne/" target="_blank">PTV.</a> Travel on trains, trams, and buses in the city require the use of a myki card.
            </li>
            <li>
                There is also an extensive <a href="https://static.ptv.vic.gov.au/siteassets/PDFs/Maps/Network-maps/PTV_FreeTramZone_Map.pdf" target="_blank">free tram zone</a> within the Melbourne CBD, which does not require a myki card.
            </li>
            <li>
                The Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre tram stop (Stop 124A Casino/MCEC) is located one stop outside this free zone from the direction of the city.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <br>
     </div>
